Function Reference/wp filter post kses « WordPress Codex
-----------

Sanitize content for allowed
[HTML](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML "wikipedia:HTML") tags for post
content.

Post content refers to the page contents of the '`post`' type and not
`$_POST` data from forms.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_filter_post_kses( $data ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$data` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Post content to filter
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Filtered post content with allowed
    [HTML](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML "wikipedia:HTML") tags and
    attributes intact.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses global: (`unknown`) `$allowedposttags`

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.0.0

Source File
-----------

`wp_filter_post_kses()` is located in `wp-includes/kses.php`.

